        <x-slot name="intro">
            <p class="mb-4">A well-signed parking lot is not just about telling people where to park — it is a direct reflection of how professionally your property is managed and how much you care about the experience of everyone who arrives at your location. Visitors and customers make quick judgments about a business based on every element of their arrival experience, and the quality of your parking signage is part of that assessment. Clear, professional parking signs reduce frustration, prevent conflicts, and create a smoother customer experience from the moment someone pulls into your lot.</p>
            <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Protect Your Property From Unauthorized Parking</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Unauthorized vehicles using your parking spaces are a genuine operational problem for businesses in commercial areas. Customer-only signs, tow-away notices, and reserved designations create a clear record of your posted rules that supports enforcement when needed. Without clearly posted signs, enforcing parking restrictions is legally difficult and practically ineffective. Properly posted, professional parking signs establish the rules clearly and reduce the frequency of parking disputes and unauthorized use.</p>
        </x-slot>
        <x-slot name="mid">
            <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Compliance and Accessibility</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">ADA-compliant accessible parking signage is a legal requirement for most commercial properties. The Americans with Disabilities Act specifies precise requirements for accessible parking sign dimensions, wording, symbol use, mounting height, and location. We produce ADA-compliant accessible parking signs that meet Illinois and federal requirements, helping you maintain code compliance and avoid potential fines or liability issues related to inadequate accessible parking designation.</p>
            <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Durability That Outlasts Cheap Alternatives</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Parking signs purchased from big box stores are often printed on low-grade materials with non-UV-resistant inks that fade, warp, and degrade quickly under Illinois weather conditions. A sign that looks faded and damaged reflects poorly on your property. Our aluminum parking signs are built for long-term outdoor use — they maintain their appearance through multiple Illinois winters and summers without significant degradation. The initial investment pays off many times over compared to repeatedly replacing inferior signs.</p>
        </x-slot>
        <x-slot name="lower">
            <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Custom Branding Opportunity</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Your parking signs do not have to look generic. Adding your business name or logo to your parking signs reinforces your brand identity at every entrance and throughout your lot, creating a more cohesive branded environment that extends from your exterior building signage all the way to the ground level of your property. Branded parking signs also communicate to visitors that this lot belongs to a specific business, which reduces confusion in shared parking areas.</p>
        </x-slot>
        <x-slot name="footer">
            <p class="mb-4">We are a veteran owned sign shop at 121 Springfield Avenue in Joliet, Illinois. We serve businesses, property managers, churches, medical facilities, and organizations throughout Will County with professional custom parking and lot signage.</p>
            <p>Call us at (815) 349 8600 to discuss your parking sign project today — single signs or complete lot signage packages.</p>
        </x-slot>
